The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Aug. 27: Risking Mamata Banerjees displeasure, ally BJP today announced that its general secretary, Biswapriya Roychow-dhury, will contest the Malda bypoll. 

 The Lok Sabha seat, which fell vacant with the death of Congress veteran Ghani Khan Chowdhury, will go to polls on September 16 .

 Durgapur: About 200 contract workers of a private steel factory here demonstrated for over four hours on Sunday demanding immediate reinstatement. Police said the management had served layoff notices on them as unit was making losses. A large police team has been deployed because of tension in the area.

 Calcutta: State Congress working president Pradip Bhattacharya has requested the chief minister to include Opposition members in the new agriculture commission. Bhattacharya said the Opposition presence will lend a democratic look to the panel set up to implement a market-driven farm policy.

 Krishnagar: PWD minister Kshiti Goswami injured his left arm on Sunday. His car hit a railing on NH 34 near Kalyani, about 40 km from Calcutta.




